<TITLE> Govt to appoint '25,000 primary school teachers' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 07 (bdnews24.com) - The government will appoint up to 25,000 primary school teachers within a short period, education minister Nurul Islam Nahid said on Tuesday. "The government will do everything since its gives highest importance to the education sector," he told parliament. Nahid said the government would establish a primary school in each upazila in phases. He also said the government has formed a high level committee to recommend regulations for inclusion of educational institutions under the MPO scheme. He said the regulations would be finalise after getting a the committee's report. bdnews
